<TEXT>
The Football World Reacts As Everton Join Liverpool In Banning The Sun From Club Premises - Pundit Arena Everton have made the decision to ban The Sun newspaper from club premises, they have announced on Twitter. 
It was done in the wake of a controversial article published by the newspaper this week regarding the incident last weekend that saw Ross Barkley assaulted in a Liverpool club. 
The newspaper is now banned by both Liverpool clubs after the red side of the city ended any relationship because of their coverage of the Hillsborough disaster. 
Today is the anniversary of that tragic day. 
The vast majority of the football world have commended the club for their actions while some pleaded with the Toffees to reverse the decision claiming banning the whole publication isn’t the solution. 
As we always knew. 
What Kelvin MacKenzie wrote about Barkley + Liverpool was crass + ignorant. 
Timing of it was sick. 
But banning a newspaper isn't the answer https://twitter.com/40YardGerrard/status/853209698773991424 Well done Everton, I don't think he was being racial about Barkley. 
However the dig about Liverpool as an area is low. 
Should be sacked. 
Sign Up For The LOI Arena Newsletter Leave this field empty if you're human: Author: The PA Team Post navigation Related posts
</TEXT>
</DOC>

