The QualityStocks Daily Newsletter   Silvore Fox Minerals Corp. 
(SFX.V) 
Today we are highlighting Silvore Fox Minerals Corp. 
( SFX.V ), here at the QualityStocks Daily Newsletter. 
Silvore Fox Minerals Corp. 
is a mineral exploration company that focuses on base and precious metal exploration projects. 
On November 17, 2010, Silvore Fox entered into a Strategic Agreement with Beijing Donia Resources Co. 
Ltd. (Donia) at the China International Mining Conference, 2010. 
Donia is the single largest shareholder of Silvore Fox. 
Donia currently holds approximately 30 percent of the Company's outstanding shares. 
Silvore Fox Minerals has their headquarters in Toronto, Ontario. 
The Company's strategic partnership with Donia provides the Corporation with a strong platform for growth through mineral exploration expertise, funding, as well as strategic acquisitions. 
Donia specializes in overseas mineral resource exploration. 
Their mandate is to establish a large-scale overseas mineral resources exploration and development base. 
Donia's majority shareholder is China Non-ferrous Metals Resource Geological Survey. 
They are a Chinese state-owned institution with more than 30 projects in Africa, the Americas, and Southeast Asia. 
Currently, Silvore Fox is active in four jurisdictions. 
These include exploring a 100 percent owned (mineral rights) Copper Porphyry system in Nova Scotia called the Coxheath Deposit, and exploring a 100 percent owned (mineral rights) Zinc-Copper-Silver-Gold VMS system in Ontario known as Pick Lake in the Winston Lake area near Schrieber. 
They also include geological due diligence on a Copper volcanic system in Madagascar which consists of two claim areas totalling over 1,700 sq km. 
(LOI stage), and geological due diligence on two Copper-Gold properties in Chile with areas totalling almost 43 sq. km. 
(LOI stage). 
This month, Silvore Fox Minerals announced the first assay results from due diligence drilling in Chile. 
As part of the Company's due diligence process before finalizing the purchase from Sinotech Mineral Exploration Chile Limitada (Sinotech) of the 100 percent interest in two Gold with Copper exploration properties in Chile, Silvore Fox has continued the programs initiated by Sinotech and performed geological work on the two properties. 
Last Wednesday, Silvore Fox Minerals announced further to their news release issued September 15, 2011 in relation to the signed letter of intent with Sinotech that the timing for the signing of the Formal Agreement to be entered into between the Corporation and Sinotech has been extended to January 6, 2012. 
Silvore Fox Minerals Corp. 
( SFX.V ) closed Thursday's trading session at $0.0850, up 13.33%, on 44,000 volume with 1,011 trades.  
The average volume for the last 60 days is 85,242.  
The 52-week low/high is $0.06/$0.25. 
Yellow Media Inc. 
(YLO.TO) 
Today we are highlighting Yellow Media Inc. 
( YLO.TO ), here at the QualityStocks Daily Newsletter. 
Yellow Media Inc. 
is Canada's #1 Internet Company via their network of companies that include Yellow Pages Group and Canpages. 
The Company owns and operates some of Canada's leading properties and publications. 
These include Yellow Pages™ directories, YellowPages.ca™, Canada411.ca™, and RedFlagDeals.com. 
The Corporation serves Canadian businesses and consumers nationwide. 
Yellow Media lists on the Toronto Stock Exchange; the Company has their headquarters in Montreal, Quebec and has offices across Canada. 
Yellow Media employs 4,143 people. 
The Company's online destinations reach approximately 9 million unique visitors monthly. 
Their mobile applications for finding local businesses and deals have undergone downloading more than 3 million times. 
In addition, Yellow Media is a leader in national digital advertising through Mediative. 
They are a digital advertising and marketing solutions provider to national agencies and advertisers. 
Yellow Media also owns Wall2Wall Media (W2W). 
They are a Yellow Pages Group (YPG) company that manages activities, publications, and services related to the real estate, employment, and hospital news print and online verticals. 
More than 80 percent of Yellow Media's revenue comes from the directory segment of their business. 
This segment generates revenues from the sale of print and online telephone directory advertising to a diversified advertiser base of more than 365,000 advertisers (excluding Canpages). 
This represents almost 35 percent of all businesses in the Corporation's markets. 
This month, the Company's Yellow Pages Group (YPG) received another distinction in the context of their digital transformation. 
This is by winning the coveted 'Best in Mobile' award at the 2011 Digi Awards for location-based services with their Yellow Pages™ mobile application. 
Since its re-launch in August 2011, the application has been downloaded close to an additional 420,000 times - boasting a significant 2.5 million downloads in total since its conception. 
It continues to top rank among productivity applications in the app store. 
The Digi Award is Yellow Pages Group's fourth prize in two months. 
Yellow Pages Group (YPG) is Canada's leading performance media and marketing solutions company. 
They serve approximately 370,000 local businesses via their nationwide sales force of over 1,200 media consultants. 
Yellow Media Inc. 
( YLO.TO ) closed Thursday's trading session at $0.18, up 9.09%, on 6,926,700 volume with 86 trades.  
Information Systems Associates Inc. 
(IOSA) 
Wall Street Resources reported last week on Information Systems Associates Inc. 
( IOSA ), and we are highlighting the Company today, here at the QualityStocks Daily Newsletter. 
Trading on the OTC Markets, Information Systems Associates Inc. 
(ISA) is a leading provider of Mobile Data Center Management™ systems and turnkey data center management solutions. 
The Company focuses on Data Center Infrastructure Management (DCIM), Data Center Data Collection, and Mobile Data Center Management. 
ISA has their corporate headquarters in Stuart, Florida. 
The Company offers Data Collection Services for the Data Center and the On Site Physical Inventory OSPI v3 System. 
The OSPI v3 System is a Mobile Data Center Asset Management product. 
It puts a data center management solution in the hand of the data center manager. 
The basis of the OSPI v3 System is on ISA's patented data center asset inventory technology. 
The Company's unique, proprietary, and patented technology, OSPI®, is a state of the art mobile system. 
Its specific design is for data center asset, inventory, and management. 
The On Site Physical Inventory®, OSPI® System, delivers Mobile Data Center Asset Management on a hand held device. 
It substantially reduces the time and effort spent managing changes to the data center, or performing asset inventories. 
It accomplishes this while greatly improving the accuracy of IT asset management data. 
ISA also has their VisionFM solution. 
Computer Aided Facilities Management (CAFM) is the management of the physical building and its contents. 
VisionFM provides software for different CAFM functions. 
This includes Asset Management, Employee and Organization Management, Space Management, Move Management and Survey Management. 
Today, ISA announced that they recently signed a software reseller and implementation services agreement with Gammagroup, Consultants en Solutions d'Affaires, Inc. 
ISA will certify Gammagroup's team on their products by the end of the year. 
Gammagroup will begin to promote ISA products and services in the first quarter of 2012. 
Mr. 
Joe Coschera, ISA's CEO, stated, "We are excited to have Gammagroup as a Partner. We anticipate that their efforts in Canada will realize revenue starting sometime in Q1 2012. With many of Canada's data centers as clients today, Gammagroup is in the position to not only offer its current core group new services and technology, but also generate new customers through the offering of ISA's OSPI Mobile Data Center Asset Management solution." 
Information Systems Associates Inc. 
( IOSA ) closed today at $0.05, even for the day, on 45,000 volume with 4 trades.  
The average volume for the last 60 days is 11,498.  
The 52-week low/high is $0.0101/$0.24. 
Generex Biotechnology Corp. 
(GNBT) 
Greenbackers and PennyTrader Publisher reported last week on Generex Biotechnology Corp. 
( GNBT ), Investor Ideas, OTCPicks, Stock Stars, PennyInvest did earlier, and today we are highlighting the Company, here at the QualityStocks Daily Newsletter. 
Trading on the OTC Bulletin Board, Generex Biotechnology Corp. 
engages in the research, development, and commercialization of drug delivery systems and technologies. 
The Company has developed a proprietary platform technology for the delivery of drugs into the human body through the oral cavity (with no deposit in the lungs). 
Their proprietary liquid formulations allow drugs normally administered by injection to be absorbed into the body by the lining of the inner mouth using Generex's proprietary RapidMist™ device. 
The Company has their corporate headquarters in Toronto, Ontario. 
Antigen Express, Inc. 
is a wholly owned subsidiary of Generex. 
This subsidiary's core platform technologies consist of immunotherapeutic vaccines for the treatment of malignant, infectious, allergic, and autoimmune diseases. 
Antigen Express has pioneered the use of specific CD4+ T-helper stimulation in immunotherapy.  
One of Antigen's platform technologies relies on inhibition of expression of the Ii protein.  
Antigen's scientists, and others, have shown clearly that suppression of expression of the Ii protein in cancer cells allows for potent stimulation of T-helper cells and prevents the further growth of cancer cells. 
Generex Biotechnology's buccal insulin spray product, Generex Oral-lyn™ is in Phase III clinical trials at several sites globally. 
Generex Oral-lyn™ is an insulin spray for the treatment of Type I and Type II diabetes. 
It is a safe, simple, fast, effective, and pain-free alternative to subcutaneous injecti
</TEXT>
