Tjx Foundation Inc - Framingham, MA funder info EIN: 04-2399760 How many hours did the grant application process take? 
4 hours 50% 50% How successfully do you think the funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Important Information 2017 Deadlines: Largest Grant: Smallest Grant: Average Grant: 3Difficult to work with2Bureaucratic2Doesn't "get" nonprofits and issues1Inadvertently exerts negative influence in the field Advice from a Friend Reviewer 9801 - Grant Applicant - applied in 2020 Our agency's mission fit into their funding priorities and guidelines. 
We were awarded a grant and invited to respond to a special RFP six months later. 
So it was a positive experience but I don't think we spoke to anyone at the foundation, communication was all through email. 
New Jersey What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Current or former grantee Funded for amount requested 2020 Average How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Good Tell us one thing that this funder does really well Helping to support homeless shelter and services.
. 
How many hours did the grant application process take? 
More than 15 Nov 18, 2020 Reviewer 5223 - Grant Applicant - applied in 2020 It's a crap-shoot. 
They will not answer emails, there is no phone number to call, and there is not even a name of a person associated with this foundation. 
And, if you're not invited to apply after doing an LOI, you will never hear back. 
Cons Massachusetts What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Current or former grantee Funded for amount requested 2020 How would you rate this funder's accessibility? 
Bad General email address and you get canned answer back - over and over again. 
No phone number, no one to call. 
Really poor communication, community relations. 
They need to clean up their act. 
How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Bad How would they know if they are accomplishing their goals if they never talk to grantees or prospective grantees? 
If you had one piece of advice to give to this funder (about grantmaking or anything else), what would it be? 
Start answering emails! 
Is there anything else that'd be useful for others to know to understand this funder? 
Don't expect to be able to communicate with them. 
the info@ email address goes into the circular file. 
Tell us one thing that this funder does really well If you are invited after an LOI, you will be given an amount to request and it almost always (always?) is awarded. 
How many hours did the grant application process take? 
4 Online eligibility questionnaire, then LOI, then full app if invited. 
Cons Inadvertently exerts negative influence in the field, Doesn't "get" nonprofits and issues, Difficult to work with, Bureaucratic Minnesota What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Applied and not funded What year was this experience? 
2018 Bad How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Average If you had one piece of advice to give to this funder (about grantmaking or anything else), what would it be? 
Please communicate with grant applicants and answer emails. 
How many hours did the grant application process take? 
0 Grant Applicant - applied in 2017 TJX is one of those opaque foundations where all communication happens through the online LOI/application portal or through an "info@" e-mail. 
I was surprised (and psyched!) when they funded our agency two years in a row, but even when they were funding us they didn't seem to want much communication. 
The LOI process is easy and painless so worth taking the chance, but our experience is that they aren't really interested in deeper relationship building. 
Massachusetts What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Current or former grantee Funded for lesser amount 2017 Average How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Average They focus on basic needs, but don't fund staff salaries which is tough. 
All agencies that work to meet basic needs rely on quality staff to be successful. 
If you had one piece of advice to give to this funder (about grantmaking or anything else), what would it be? 
Make your contacts at the foundation less anonymous-- it helps us nonprofit folks tremendously to know we can connect with a real human rather than a do-not-reply e-mail. 
Tell us one thing that this funder does really well They are awesome at keeping their grant reports short and sweet! 
They also funded us for 2 years in a row, which really helped our program grow. 
How many hours did the grant application process take? 
0 Reviewer 6099 - Grant Applicant - applied in 2018 The TJX Foundation requires an LOI before doing a full application, which is great. 
However, they claim to not be able to let you know if your LOI is NOT chosen. 
But they don't post a date by which you should hear if your LOI is chosen. 
They ALSO make it clear that they don't want you to contact them about the status of your LOI. 
So...if you have a pending LOI, you just...keep....
waiting. 
Cons Array What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Grant currently pending What year was this experience? 
2018 How would you rate this funder's accessibility? 
Bad They provide no guidelines of how long you will have to wait to hear back on your LOI and they make it clear they don't want you to contact them. 
This lack of communication makes it difficult for nonprofits. 
How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Average If their goal is to string nonprofits along while they make up their minds, they are killin' it. 
If you had one piece of advice to give to this funder (about grantmaking or anything else), what would it be? 
Post something on your website that says, "We will contact you to invite a full proposal by [XXX date]. If you don't hear from us by then, we were not able to move your application forward at this time." 
Tell us one thing that this funder does really well Requires an LOI first. 
More than 15 Oct 06, 2017 Grant Applicant - applied in 2016 It is unfortunate that their online grant system is fraught with bugs and glitches. 
Their tech support insists the problem is at our end rather than trying to help us fix the problem and access our application. 
Furthermore, a phone call to the Foundation is futile. 
You will hear a recording that says, "Due to a high volume of callers, please email your questions to . . ." 
We are not getting a satisfactory response from their tech support on email. 
Very frustrating! 
Cons Minnesota What is your relationship with the funder for this experience? 
Current or former grantee Funded for amount requested 2016 How would you rate this funder's accessibility? 
Bad We were funded over a year ago. 
Unless the Foundation fixes its broken links, we will not be able to reapply for funding. 
I presume the TJX Foundation is accomplishing its current goals. 
How successfully do you think this funder is accomplishing its current philanthropic goals? 
Average If you had one piece of advice to give to this funder (about grantmaking or anything else), what would it be? 
Fix your website! 
Please care about your grantees and potential grantees by helping them access your online system instead of denying that there's a problem. 
How many hours did the grant application process take? 
Less than 5 Would you like to share your experiences about this funder?
